Ah, that one is easy: Your header item is defining a function "wbAction". With deferred items this function is now defined inside the 'DOMContentLoaded' callback only.

This is one of the corner cases that can be solved in client only:

```
	private static StringBuilder getNamedFunctionStr(String name, AbstractDefaultAjaxBehavior b, CallbackParameter... extraParameters) {
		StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
		sb.append("window.").append(name).append(" = function(");
		boolean first = true;
		for (CallbackParameter curExtraParameter : extraParameters) {
			if (curExtraParameter.getFunctionParameterName() != null) {
				if (first) {
					first = false;
				} else {
					sb.append(',');
				}
				sb.append(curExtraParameter.getFunctionParameterName());
			}
		}
		sb.append(") {\n");
		sb.append(b.getCallbackFunctionBody(extraParameters));
		sb.append("}\n;");
		return sb;
	}
```

